  "body": "### Description\r\n\r\n*Type*: Bug\r\n\r\n*Summary*: `Send` button is active when having spaces only in text box on Statis desktop. When i hit Enter - nothing is actually sent. There is no harm of such behavior, however, it would be great to align desktop and mobile client.\r\n\r\n#### Expected behavior\r\nHere some patterns from some messengers:\r\n\r\n1. Status mobile: `send` is not active when having only spaces in text box\r\n2. Viber desktop: `send` is active when having only spaces in text box however hitting send does not actually send this message\r\n3. Watsapp desktop: not able to enter spaces only within desktop. If i copypaste them and try to send - hitting enter does not send such message\r\n\r\n#### Actual behavior\r\n\r\nI am able to enter spaces only in the text box of Status desktop  (1x1 chat) and send button is enabled however hitting send does not send it actually. \r\n\r\n![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/28752642/46413924-b2f8be00-c72a-11e8-884e-d3a87fce0abb.png)\r\n\r\n \r\n### Reproduction\r\n\r\n- Open Status desktop\r\n- Add any contact\r\n- Enter spaces only in the text field and hit enter",
